  <thing id="psPUCaringHands1" name="Caring Hands" description="You must be a highlord following the tenets of cultivation to manifest this power. You cannot learn this power with the Expanded Knowledge feat or similar abilities.\n\nWhen you use this power, you can remove a condition or damage affecting a member of your collective, based on how many powers points were spent on the power. Choose one option from the following table to treat:\n\n{b}1 PP:{/b} Compulsion or charm, up to 4 hit points + 2 hit points per pp spent augmenting the power\n{b}3 PP:{/b} Fatigue, paralysis, poison, up to 4 points of ability damage\n{b}5 PP:{/b} Blindness, deafness, disease\n{b}7 PP:{/b} Up to 2 points of ability drain, up to 1 negative level\n{b}9 PP:{/b} Curses, enchantment and telepathy effects, transmutation and psychometabolism effects\n{b}11 PP:{/b} Lost limbs, petrification\n\nIn order to treat a magical effect, you must succeed at a manifester level check (1d20 + your manifester level) against a DC of 11 + the effect&apos;s caster level, and in order to treat a curse, disease, or poison, you must succeed at a manifester level check against the condition&apos;s save DC." compset="PsiPower">
    <fieldval field="psiAugText" value="This power can be augmented in one or more of the following ways.{br}{br}• For every additional power point you spend, allies you affect with this power gain 2 temporary hit points. These temporary hit points last for 1 minute or until used.{br}{br}• For every 2 power points you spend, you gain a +1 bonus on your manifester level checks to remove conditions that require a check.{br}{br}• For every 2 power points you spend, you can affect an additional creature, curing them of the same conditions or amount of damage.{br}{br}• For ever 4 power points you spend, you can remove another condition. You may only choose a given type of damage once per use of this power (for example, if you spent 3 power points, you could heal 8 hit points and remove the ally&apos;s fatigue, but could not choose “hit points” twice to heal more hit points)."/>
    <fieldval field="sRange" value="Collective (see text)"/>
    <fieldval field="sTarget" value="One member of your collective"/>
    <usesource source="srcPUAuHil"/>
